Comment: Man, so many people bashed WWII. For me personally, it was my first ever Call of Duty. None of the futuristic-style Call of Duty‚Äôs had interested me, but WWII gave me different vibes. I love the history behind WWII, and Activision hadn‚Äôt made a proper game set in WWII since World At War. I was hooked by the game, and in the end I had leveled up all the way to Prestige Master. Yes, the game has a lot of flaws and Sledgehammer played it too safe, but they really improved the game over its life span. I played from release all the way to the final DLC and in-game event. Over all that time, the biggest problem was that everyone stopped playing after release, because that‚Äôs when the game kinda sucked. It really makes me sad that nobody stuck around to see all the great additions Sledgehammer added to the game after release. If you haven‚Äôt gotten on WWII since launch, I highly recommend you do, if you can find a lobby. I‚Äôm sure you‚Äôd be surprised with how fun the game actually became. I‚Äôm sure everyone still hates the game and will bash me over my opinion, but damn, I really did like this game and I‚Äôm gonna miss it, now that BO4 is the hot new Call of Duty. Thanks for all the fun WWII.

Title: Official Call of Duty¬Æ: WWII Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Sad. 

I've waited so long for a new WW2 cod to happen, just to see this abomination.

It's the same old spray and pray, rushing around without any sense and tactics kiddie shooter as in the last 10 years before.
Every kill triggers tons of useless award / notification emblems, like you are at the academy awards and not in a war. seriously who needs all that garbage. 

But yeah, you can already tell it's cancer when you start an FPS on a gaming pc and it's asking you if you want to play with a controller. 

Too many useless menus and customization options. No dedicated servers.

And a uav, red dot sights in a ww2 game... seriously?

Graphics look like from 2010, still the game is lagging for me.
Gameplay feels like you are playing Quake 3 Arena and not a world war 2 shooter, it's too fast.

Can't say anything positive about it except that it's good that there is a chance to try this for free before wasting 60‚Ç¨'s for the final product.

If you want a good Call of Duty, buy cod 1 or 2 for the great sp campain, or 4 for great multiplayer, or cod 5 world at war for an awesome 4 player coop campain, every cod game afterwards is trash for console heros or kids.

Rest in Peace Call of Duty, may you die for good this time.

Title: Official Call of Duty¬Æ: WWII Reveal Trailer
Comment:
okay, I hope I'm not the only one who sees the historical inaccuracies and political correctness in this game. I see censored swastikas, I see flamethrowers that were very rarely used in Europe during WW2, and I see African American troops who were in segregated units and rarely ever saw combat. I also hear that there are female soldiers, which makes sense only for The French
 Resistance, but in no other places did women ever see combat. Getting back to the Swastikas, how can you leave out Swastikas which was a major part of WW2, If you think that history should be censored for the sole reason that it may offend somebody, you're a fool and a dimwit. That also goes for including women in combat, I do not agree that Nazism was good nor will I ever. Also I do believe that women should not have been excluded from combat. BUT THAT WAS THE TIMES AND TIMES HAVE SINCE CHANGED. But given that times have changed, that does not mean that anyone has the right to blur out and censor history. We need to instead embrace that the atrocities of The Holocaust and WW2 did occur and remember those dark times so that they do not happen again. Now if you are reading this and think that I am a closed minded bigoted old man, think again, I am a young adult with a passion for history and the preservation of history.  That is all I have to say for now.

Title: Official Call of Duty¬Æ: WWII Reveal Trailer
Comment: I want psychology to play a role in this game's story. If you think about it, has there ever been a call of duty character who has expressed remorse for the people they've killed? And by the end of the campaign most main character have probably killed hundreds maybe thousands. In real life a very small percentage of soldiers can kill without having any mental consequences. I want things like dehumanization, PTSD, extremely brutal deaths, racism, etc. In my opinion the campaign will not be good if it glorifies war like almost every other cod. You can't glorify ww2 there's no glory in it, waw did a good job at this, but like said previously it's extremely unrealistic that not one character ever felt remorse for killing. I'm not racist but I really want racism to be in this game. Studies show that racism flourishes in war because soldiers subconsciously attempt to detach themselves from their enemies. Call of duty needs to stop telling a story and tell a story that MEANS something. I want them to show two things in this cod: 1) life is precious 2) life is susceptible and vulnerable
